section.section:
The provisions of paragraph (a) of this subsection shall not apply to temporary amusement rides or amusement attractions that:
Operate in connection with the sanctioned public fair or exposition;
Operate at a public fair or exposition that is in a contiguous county, is sanctioned by the Department of Agriculture, and is under the authority of a public fair association;
Operate under the authority of a religious or educational organization;
Operate more than thirty (30) days before or seven (7) days after the sanctioned public fair or exposition;
Are clown acts, local festivals, or amusement or entertainment shows with six (6) or fewer kiddie rides; or
Operated as a nonprofit or charitable organization in this state before March 10, 2003.
